Paper: hep-th/0102068

Date: 2001-02-13

Title: Stability of bound states in the light-front Yukawa model

Authors: M. Mangin-Brinet, J. Carbonell and V.A. Karmanov

Comments: 5 pages, 2 figures, submitted to publication

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D64 (2001) 027701

We show that in the system of two fermions interacting by scalar exchange,the solutions for J$^{\pi}$=$0^+$ bound states are stable without any cutoffregularization for coupling constant below some critical value.